{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The total median, however, was 37 individuals, indicating a more representative measure.",
    "The sample size was aligned with the same quality trend observed for the type of evaluation, with the following means (M) and medians (Md): Preservation M = 50 Md = 23, Musealization M = 120 Md = 37, and Education M = 209 Md = 72.",
    "Similarly, Preservation had the smallest samples, while Musealization and especially Education had the largest ones.",
    "This finding is aligned with those of other studies indicating that evaluations conducted in museums and similar environments often involve large samples [163].",
    "Education, on the other hand, is an area that typically stands out for the robustness of its evaluations [4]."
  ],
